# IVB Digital - Design System & Architecture Guidelines

## Brand Identity

- **Company**: IVB Digital
- **Type**: B2B Agency Website
- **Primary Purpose**: Demonstrate expertise, professionalism, and credibility
- **Target Audience**: B2B companies (marketing and revenue teams) seeking marketing services

## Services Offered

- **Strategy & Consulting**: GTM strategy, positioning, messaging, analytics strategy
- **Performance Marketing**: PPC (Google, LinkedIn), paid social, retargeting
- **Social & Content**: Organic social, content production, thought leadership enablement
- **Creative**: Brand and campaign design, ad creative, motion/interactive
- **Web Development**: Next.js/React, design systems, CRO, CMS integration
- **SEO**: Technical SEO, on-page optimization, content strategy
- **Analytics & RevOps**: Tracking, dashboards, attribution, automation

## Color Palette

- **White**: Primary background color (#FFFFFF)
- **Black**: Primary text color (#000000 or #171717)
- **Royal Purple**: Accent/brand color (#6B46C1 or #7C3AED - adjust as needed)
- **Usage**: Use white space liberally. Purple should be used sparingly for CTAs, highlights, and key interactive elements.

## Design Principles

### Minimalism

- Clean, uncluttered layouts
- Generous white space is essential - never feel cramped
- Remove unnecessary elements
- Focus on clarity and readability

### White Space

- Use generous padding and margins (minimum 2rem/32px between major sections)
- Sections should breathe - allow content to stand alone
- White space is a design element, not empty space
- Mobile: Maintain white space even on smaller screens (minimum 1rem/16px)

### Typography

- Use clean, modern sans-serif fonts
- Large, readable headings
- Generous line-height for readability (minimum 1.6)
- Clear hierarchy: H1 > H2 > H3 > Body
- Avoid decorative fonts - keep it professional

### Visual Hierarchy

- Use size, weight, and color to establish hierarchy
- Purple accents should guide the eye to important elements
- Black text on white background for maximum readability
- Subtle use of purple for emphasis only

## Architecture & File Structure

### Component-Based Architecture

- **Every page** is composed of multiple components
- **Each component** represents a distinct section of the page
- **Each section component** lives in its own file
- **All section components** are located in the `src/components/sections/` directory

### File Structure Pattern

```
src/
  app/
    [page]/
      page.tsx          # Page file that imports and arranges sections
  components/
    common/             # Site-wide common components (navbar, footer, etc.)
      Navbar.tsx
      Footer.tsx
    sections/           # All section components live here
      HeroSection.tsx
      AboutSection.tsx
      ServicesSection.tsx
      etc.
    ui/                 # Reusable UI components (buttons, cards, etc.)
      Button.tsx
      Card.tsx
      etc.
```

### Component Naming Convention

- Section components: `[Name]Section.tsx` (e.g., `HeroSection.tsx`, `ServicesSection.tsx`)
- UI components: PascalCase (e.g., `Button.tsx`, `Card.tsx`)
- Use descriptive, semantic names

### Page Structure Pattern

```tsx
// Example: src/app/about/page.tsx
import HeroSection from "@/components/sections/HeroSection";
import AboutSection from "@/components/sections/AboutSection";
import CtaSection from "@/components/sections/CtaSection";

export default function AboutPage() {
  return (
    <main>
      <HeroSection />
      <AboutSection />
      <CtaSection />
    </main>
  );
}
```

### Section Component Pattern

```tsx
// Example: src/components/sections/HeroSection.tsx
export default function HeroSection() {
  return <section className="py-20 px-4">{/* Section content */}</section>;
}
```

## Spacing System

- Use Tailwind's spacing scale consistently
- Section padding: `py-16` to `py-32` (64px to 128px vertical)
- Container padding: `px-4` to `px-8` (16px to 32px horizontal)
- Gap between elements: `gap-8` to `gap-16` (32px to 64px)
- Minimum spacing between sections: `py-16` (64px)

## Component Guidelines

### Buttons

- Primary: Royal purple background, white text
- Secondary: White background, royal purple border and text
- Use generous padding: `px-8 py-4` minimum
- Rounded corners: `rounded-lg` or `rounded-xl`
- Hover states: Subtle opacity or scale changes

### Cards

- White background with subtle shadow or border
- Generous padding: `p-6` to `p-8`
- Rounded corners: `rounded-xl`
- Ample spacing between cards: `gap-6` to `gap-8`

### Typography Scale

- H1: `text-4xl` to `text-6xl` (36px to 60px)
- H2: `text-3xl` to `text-4xl` (30px to 36px)
- H3: `text-2xl` to `text-3xl` (24px to 30px)
- Body: `text-base` to `text-lg` (16px to 18px)
- Small: `text-sm` (14px)

## Mobile Optimization

**Critical**: Every page must be fully optimized for mobile devices. Mobile traffic is essential for B2B sites.

### Mobile-First Approach

- Design for mobile first, then enhance for larger screens
- Breakpoints: sm (640px), md (768px), lg (1024px), xl (1280px)
- Test on actual devices, not just browser dev tools
- Ensure touch targets are at least 44x44px (minimum tap size)

### Responsive Layout Guidelines

- Stack sections vertically on mobile
- Use responsive typography: `text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl`
- Maintain white space on all screen sizes (minimum 1rem/16px on mobile)
- Horizontal padding: `px-4` on mobile, `px-8` on desktop
- Vertical padding: `py-12` on mobile, `py-20` on desktop

### Mobile-Specific Considerations

- **Navigation**: Use hamburger menu on mobile, full nav on desktop
- **Images**: Optimize for mobile bandwidth, use Next.js Image with responsive sizes
- **Forms**: Full-width inputs on mobile, constrained width on desktop
- **Buttons**: Full-width on mobile (`w-full md:w-auto`), auto-width on desktop
- **Text**: Maximum line length of 75 characters on desktop, full width on mobile
- **Tables**: Consider horizontal scroll or card layout on mobile
- **Videos**: Ensure responsive embed containers

### Performance on Mobile

- Minimize JavaScript bundle size
- Use code splitting for heavy components
- Optimize images for mobile (use `srcset` and `sizes`)
- Lazy load below-the-fold content
- Minimize render-blocking resources
- Target Lighthouse mobile score of 90+

### Touch Interactions

- Ensure all interactive elements are easily tappable
- Add adequate spacing between clickable elements
- Use touch-friendly hover states (consider tap states)
- Test swipe gestures where appropriate
- Avoid hover-only interactions on mobile

## SEO Optimization

**Critical**: What good is a website if no one can find it? SEO is non-negotiable.

### Technical SEO

- **Meta Tags**: Every page must have unique `<title>` and `<meta name="description">`
- **Open Graph**: Include OG tags for social sharing (title, description, image, url)
- **Structured Data**: Use JSON-LD schema markup (Organization, WebSite, BreadcrumbList, Article, etc.)
- **Canonical URLs**: Set canonical tags to prevent duplicate content
- **Robots.txt**: Properly configured for search engine crawling
- **Sitemap.xml**: Generate and submit XML sitemap
- **HTTPS**: Ensure SSL certificate is active
- **Page Speed**: Target Core Web Vitals (LCP < 2.5s, FID < 100ms, CLS < 0.1)

### Next.js SEO Implementation

```tsx
// Example: src/app/about/page.tsx
import { Metadata } from "next";

export const metadata: Metadata = {
  title: "About IVB Digital | Digital Marketing Agency",
  description:
    "Learn about IVB Digital, a leading B2B digital marketing agency specializing in...",
  openGraph: {
    title: "About IVB Digital | Digital Marketing Agency",
    description: "Learn about IVB Digital...",
    images: ["/og-image.jpg"],
  },
  alternates: {
    canonical: "https://ivbdigital.com/about",
  },
};
```

### Content SEO

- **Keyword Research**: Target relevant B2B marketing keywords
- **Heading Structure**: Use proper H1-H6 hierarchy (one H1 per page)
- **Internal Linking**: Link between related pages and sections
- **Alt Text**: Descriptive alt text for all images
- **URL Structure**: Clean, descriptive URLs (`/services/digital-marketing` not `/page?id=123`)
- **Content Quality**: Original, valuable content that demonstrates expertise
- **Content Length**: Aim for comprehensive content (1000+ words for main pages)

### On-Page SEO Checklist

- ✅ Unique, keyword-rich title tag (50-60 characters)
- ✅ Compelling meta description (150-160 characters)
- ✅ One H1 tag per page with primary keyword
- ✅ Proper heading hierarchy (H2, H3, etc.)
- ✅ Keyword usage in first paragraph
- ✅ Internal links to related content
- ✅ External links to authoritative sources
- ✅ Image alt attributes with relevant keywords
- ✅ Fast page load time (< 3 seconds)
- ✅ Mobile-friendly design
- ✅ Schema markup for rich snippets

### Local SEO (if applicable)

- Google Business Profile optimization
- NAP (Name, Address, Phone) consistency
- Local keywords in content
- Location pages if multiple locations

### SEO Best Practices

- **Semantic HTML**: Use proper HTML5 semantic elements (`<header>`, `<nav>`, `<main>`, `<article>`, `<section>`, `<footer>`)
- **Accessibility**: SEO and accessibility go hand-in-hand
- **Mobile-First Indexing**: Google primarily uses mobile version for indexing
- **Page Speed**: Fast sites rank better
- **Fresh Content**: Regularly update and add new content
- **User Experience**: Low bounce rate signals quality to search engines
- **Backlinks**: Quality over quantity (though this is more marketing than dev)

### SEO Tools & Monitoring

- Set up Google Search Console
- Set up Google Analytics 4
- Monitor Core Web Vitals
- Track keyword rankings
- Monitor crawl errors
- Review search performance regularly

### Common SEO Mistakes to Avoid

- ❌ Duplicate content across pages
- ❌ Missing or duplicate title tags
- ❌ Poor URL structure
- ❌ Slow page load times
- ❌ Not mobile-friendly
- ❌ Missing alt text on images
- ❌ Broken internal links
- ❌ Thin or duplicate content
- ❌ Keyword stuffing
- ❌ Ignoring Core Web Vitals

## Performance

- Optimize images (use Next.js Image component)
- Lazy load sections below the fold when appropriate
- Keep components focused and single-purpose
- Use TypeScript for type safety

## Accessibility

- Maintain proper heading hierarchy
- Use semantic HTML elements
- Ensure sufficient color contrast (black on white, purple on white)
- Add alt text to all images
- Keyboard navigation support
- ARIA labels where appropriate

## Code Quality

- Use TypeScript for all components
- Export components as default exports
- Use functional components with proper typing
- Keep components focused and reusable
- Add JSDoc comments for complex components

## Purple Color Usage

- Use purple for:
  - Primary CTAs and buttons
  - Links and hover states
  - Accent highlights
  - Brand elements (logo, icons)
- Avoid:
  - Large purple backgrounds (use sparingly)
  - Purple text on dark backgrounds
  - Overuse that competes with content

## Content Strategy

- Focus on demonstrating expertise
- Use case studies and testimonials
- Show process and methodology
- Clear value propositions
- Professional, confident tone
- Avoid jargon - be clear and direct

## Animation & Interactions

- Subtle, purposeful animations only
- Smooth transitions (200-300ms)
- Avoid distracting motion
- Use for: hover states, scroll reveals, micro-interactions
- Keep it minimal and professional

## Do's and Don'ts

### Do:

- ✅ Use generous white space
- ✅ Keep layouts clean and minimal
- ✅ Use purple sparingly for accents
- ✅ Create separate section components
- ✅ Maintain consistent spacing
- ✅ Focus on readability
- ✅ Show expertise through content
- ✅ Test on mobile devices (not just dev tools)
- ✅ Optimize for mobile performance
- ✅ Add SEO metadata to every page
- ✅ Use semantic HTML elements
- ✅ Optimize images for web
- ✅ Test page speed and Core Web Vitals

### Don't:

- ❌ Clutter layouts
- ❌ Overuse purple color
- ❌ Create cramped sections
- ❌ Mix concerns in components
- ❌ Use decorative fonts
- ❌ Add unnecessary animations
- ❌ Compromise white space for content
- ❌ Ignore mobile optimization
- ❌ Skip SEO metadata
- ❌ Use generic or missing alt text
- ❌ Create slow-loading pages
- ❌ Forget to test on actual devices

## Development Workflow

1. Create page file in `src/app/[route]/page.tsx`
2. Add SEO metadata (title, description, OG tags) to page file
3. Create section components in `src/components/sections/`
4. Import and arrange sections in page file
5. Style with Tailwind using design system guidelines
6. **Mobile Testing**: Test on actual mobile devices and responsive breakpoints
7. **SEO Check**: Verify meta tags, heading hierarchy, alt text, and structured data
8. **Performance**: Test page speed and Core Web Vitals (Lighthouse)
9. Ensure accessibility standards
10. Validate HTML semantics and proper heading structure
